UML:ClassifierRole.name: General requirements
PWF vehicle state concept
Log and Trace
Partial Networking
RSE
The Head Unit must support the Parken/Wohnen/Fahren (PWF) ve

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Head Unit must support the Parken/Wohnen/Fahren (PWF) vehicle state concept.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The HeadUnit must provide different modes which are describe

UML:TaggedValue.value: The HeadUnit must provide different modes which are described below BMW provides reference implementations in C for the Statemachine. The reference implementations are generated out of a Rhapsody model. The supplier shall integrate these reference implementations. The responsibilities are the same as for the BMW MMI-EE: BMW is responsible for fixing bugs within the provided components itself, while the supplier is responsible for clean integration and fixing any integration related problems. Any required changes shall be agreed with BMW.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: There are several applications in the Head Unit which must r

UML:TaggedValue.value: There are several applications in the Head Unit which must request Partial Network Requests. The Head Unit must send an aggregated Partial Network Request to the Partial Network Master.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Selective Wakeup functionality
System time is not available on I&K-CAN during Autonomous En

UML:TaggedValue.value: System time is not available on I&K-CAN during Autonomous Entertainment Operation. The Head Unit must increment the system time by itself (requirement "Systimeclient" in LH Diagnosemaster)

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Partial Network Operation
The Head Unit must support partial networking with CAN on /

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Head Unit must support partial networking with CAN on / Ethernet off or vice versa. There should be no automatically "wake-through" between the busses when it is not necessary.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: In Autonomous Entertainment Operation, only I&K domain is ac

UML:TaggedValue.value: In Autonomous Entertainment Operation, only I&K domain is active (=partial network "Entertainment"). All other busses are going to sleep.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: In Autonomous Entertainment Operation, certain boardnet mess

UML:TaggedValue.value: In Autonomous Entertainment Operation, certain boardnet messages from devices on other busses are not available.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Head Unit must renew the request of Partial Network "Ent

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Head Unit must renew the request of Partial Network "Entertainment" periodically.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Head Unit must renew the request of Partial Network "Ent

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Head Unit must renew the request of Partial Network "Entertainment" periodically.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Head Unit must release the request for Partial Network

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Head Unit must release the request for Partial Network Entertainment when Entertainment Mode is left.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Head Unit must release the request for Partial Network

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Head Unit must release the request for Partial Network Entertainment when Application Mode is left.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Head Unit must request the Partial Network "Entertainmen

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Head Unit must request the Partial Network "Entertainment" when Application Mode is entered.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Head Unit must request the Partial Network "Entertainmen

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Head Unit must request the Partial Network "Entertainment" when Entertainment Mode is entered.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The assembled CAN-transceiver must support selective wakeup

UML:TaggedValue.value: The assembled CAN-transceiver must support selective wakeup functionality.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The configured CAN transceiver wakes up the Head Unit only w

UML:TaggedValue.value: The configured CAN transceiver wakes up the Head Unit only when Head Unit functionality is required.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The central vehicle state management provides the informatio

UML:TaggedValue.value: The central vehicle state management provides the information whether the Head Unit functionality is required or not.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The CAN transceiver must be powered by Clamp 30f as long as

UML:TaggedValue.value: The CAN transceiver must be powered by Clamp 30f as long as headunit is in InstantOn Mode, so that selective wakeup is also possible in InstantOn Mode.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The selective wakeup capable CAN transceiver must be configu

UML:TaggedValue.value: The selective wakeup capable CAN transceiver must be configured each time after the power supply was interrupted.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Head Unit must fulfill the corresponding requirements in

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Head Unit must fulfill the corresponding requirements in the ABK LH.

The Entertainment Mode must be able to substitute the clamp

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Entertainment Mode must be able to substitute the clamp R operation known from the conventional clamp concept.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: During StandbyScreen, FBM preview must be shown when custome

UML:TaggedValue.value: During StandbyScreen, FBM preview must be shown when customer touches the FBM buttons.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Head Unit enters the WelcomeAnimation Mode when it takes

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Head Unit enters the WelcomeAnimation Mode when it takes part at the syncronized Welcome Animation.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: In SleepDelay Mode, Headunit is internally on (all applicati

UML:TaggedValue.value: In SleepDelay Mode, Headunit is internally on (all applications are available) but Display is off and bus is off.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The SleepDelay Mode is entered when state "Standfunktion" is

UML:TaggedValue.value: The SleepDelay Mode is entered when state "Standfunktion" is active, busses go to sleep and delayMode is coded as sleepDelay mode.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Entertainment Mode is left when State Wohnen is left.

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Entertainment Mode is left when State Wohnen is left.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Application Mode
The active applications/functions in Shutdown Mode are ident

UML:TaggedValue.value: The active applications/functions in Shutdown Mode are identical to Communication Mode.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: It must be possible to cancel the WelcomeAnimation Mode when

UML:TaggedValue.value: It must be possible to cancel the WelcomeAnimation Mode when vehicle leaves Wohnen-state (e.g. customer starts engine)

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Powerdown Mode
The FeTra Mode provides no function for the Customer (e.g. N

UML:TaggedValue.value: The FeTra Mode provides no function for the Customer (e.g. Navigation, Entertainment....), except PDC audio. The list of the active functions is administrated by BMW Energiebordnetz-department and will be provided to the supplier by BMW.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: User Off States:
When the key state changes to "no authorization" during Ente

UML:TaggedValue.value: When the key state changes to "no authorization" during Entertainment Mode, Bluetooth is disconnected (independent from any call activity).

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Entertainment Mode is entered when vehicle state changes

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Entertainment Mode is entered when vehicle state changes from Fahren to Wohnen

UML:ClassifierRole.name: In this case, the StandbyScreen is entered after Welcome Ani

UML:TaggedValue.value: In this case, the StandbyScreen is entered after Welcome Animation is finished.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: In Entertainment Mode, the Bluetooth connection is establish

UML:TaggedValue.value: In Entertainment Mode, the Bluetooth connection is established only when authorization is given by key state.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: This mode can be entered from any other mode for a diagnosti

UML:TaggedValue.value: This mode can be entered from any other mode for a diagnostic triggered reset. In this mode persistent data relevant to diagnosis has to be written. For more information see LH Diagnose

UML:TaggedValue.value: The following operation diagram shows the main states and transitions which are required to fulfill the "Parken/Wohnen/Fahren" ABK.

Diagnosis States
When the Powerdown diagnosis command is received during vehi

UML:TaggedValue.value: When the Powerdown diagnosis command is received during vehicle states "Fahren" or "Prfen/Analyse/Diagnose", the Powerdown Mode is entered after vehicle has left this states.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: In Application Mode, the Bluetooth connection is established

UML:TaggedValue.value: In Application Mode, the Bluetooth connection is established without checking the authorization state.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: In StandbyScreen, Head Unit must be able to wake up the buss

UML:TaggedValue.value: In StandbyScreen, Head Unit must be able to wake up the busses when customer interaction (e.g. via Touchscreen) is detected.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Welcome Animation (including Standby screen)

UML:TaggedValue.value: There must be only one Software Module which calculates the Headunit Mode.

Reset Mode
The GoodbyeAnimation Mode is left when the Goodbye Animation

UML:TaggedValue.value: The GoodbyeAnimation Mode is left when the Goodbye Animation is finished.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The GoodbyeAnimation Mode is left when vehicle gets locked.

UML:TaggedValue.value: The GoodbyeAnimation Mode is left when vehicle gets locked.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Comments: FeTra = Production (Fertigung) and Transport For m

UML:TaggedValue.value: Comments: FeTra = Production (Fertigung) and Transport For more information please see DOC31 - LH Diagnose

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Tempshutdown Mode must be entered when a critical temper

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Tempshutdown Mode must be entered when a critical temperature is reached to protect components from damage.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Comments: Normal startup must be possible after this shutdow

UML:TaggedValue.value: Comments: Normal startup must be possible after this shutdown. For more info please see DOC31 - LH Diagnose

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The applications must not look on the PWF state in order to

UML:TaggedValue.value: The applications must not look on the PWF state in order to get the system state. They must look on the Headunit Mode.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The SleepDelay Mode is left when - bus gets activated - the

UML:TaggedValue.value: The SleepDelay Mode is left when - bus gets activated - the internal timer ("StayInMode-Timer") of 3 minutes expires (with "Standfunktionen" expired)

UML:ClassifierRole.name: User On States:
The required Head Unit states are classified in "User Off-",

UML:TaggedValue.value: The required Head Unit states are classified in "User Off-", "User On-" and "Diagnosis-states". The WelcomeAnimation Mode and the StandbyScreen Mode are assigned to the User Off-states as no customer functionality is provided in this states although display is on.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Application Mode is entered when vehicle state "Fahren"

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Application Mode is entered when vehicle state "Fahren" or "Prfen/Analyse/Diagnose" is reached.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: In StandbyScreen, Head Unit is internally on (all applicatio

UML:TaggedValue.value: In StandbyScreen, Head Unit is internally on (all applications are available) but display shows only a standby screen.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: During Entertainment Mode, a short press on the Entertainmen

UML:TaggedValue.value: During Entertainment Mode, a short press on the Entertainmentbutton provides mute-funtionality and must not terminate the Entertainment Mode (contrary to the conventional clamp concept behaviour)

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The actual headunit-mode has to be provided to the rest of t

UML:TaggedValue.value: The actual headunit-mode has to be provided to the rest of the headunitsystem through the corresponding Ethernet service. The applications must use the mode indicator, not the vehicle state signals from the bus.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Communication Mode
The FeTra-Mode is set and reset by diagnostic command, indep

UML:TaggedValue.value: The FeTra-Mode is set and reset by diagnostic command, independent from vehicle PWF status

UML:ClassifierRole.name: When Carsharing is coded, the Carsharing Logout-Screen must

UML:TaggedValue.value: When Carsharing is coded, the Carsharing Logout-Screen must be shown instead of the Goodbye Animation.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The SleepDelay Mode must not be entered when Head Unit is in

UML:TaggedValue.value: The SleepDelay Mode must not be entered when Head Unit is in KISU Mode.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The InstantOn mode is entered when delayMode InstantOn is co

UML:TaggedValue.value: The InstantOn mode is entered when delayMode InstantOn is coded.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Shutdown Mode
The Shutdown Mode is entered when Head Unit is ready for shu

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Shutdown Mode is entered when Head Unit is ready for shutdown and does not need bus activity anymore.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Sleep Delay Mode
It must be possible to take or to reject an incoming call du

UML:TaggedValue.value: It must be possible to take or to reject an incoming call during display of Standby-Screen. Therefore, Bluetooth connection must be established when authorization is given. After an incoming call is rejected or hung up by the customer, Entertainment audio must not be replayed automatically.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: In Flash Mode, all Flash functionality must be provided.

UML:TaggedValue.value: In Flash Mode, all Flash functionality must be provided.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: <Picture> (binary content)

UML:TaggedValue.value: <Picture> (DOORS contains binary content here which has not been transmitted to EA)

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Power Down Mode must be entered when Powerdown diagnosis

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Power Down Mode must be entered when Powerdown diagnosis command is received and vehicle state "Fahren" or "Prfen/Diagnose" is not active.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: In StandbyScreen, Head Unit does not request Partial Network

UML:TaggedValue.value: In StandbyScreen, Head Unit does not request Partial Network and does not keep the bus alive. The Vehicle State Master (in the BDC) is responsible for keeping the bus alive only when it is necessary, e.g. for faster FBM preview.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The StandbyScreen is entered when vehicle state "Wohnen" is

UML:TaggedValue.value: The StandbyScreen is entered when vehicle state "Wohnen" is reached except Kombi sends a signal that CID must stay black until Welcome Animation trigger is received.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Communication Mode is entered when bus activity is detec

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Communication Mode is entered when bus activity is detected but Infotainment system is still user off.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: To provide a fast startup in most of the usecases, an Instan

UML:TaggedValue.value: To provide a fast startup in most of the usecases, an Instant-on state must be provided.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Instand-on Mode
The Entertainment Mode is entered when an E-Call is started

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Entertainment Mode is entered when an E-Call is started during any other state except Application Mode and Diagnosis Modes.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: For further requirements and information, please see chapter

UML:TaggedValue.value: For further requirements and information, please see chapter "3.4. Instant on"

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Head Unit stays in Instand-on mode until the timer expir

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Head Unit stays in Instand-on mode until the timer expires or another state is requested.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The PWF concept defines that it is clear for the customer, i

UML:TaggedValue.value: The PWF concept defines that it is clear for the customer, in which state the car is. The Wohnen state is characterized by showing system-readiness to the customer. This means, among other things, showing a standby screen in the Kombi-display and in the CID.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Flash Mode
The GoodbyeAnimation Mode is left when vehicle state "Standf

UML:TaggedValue.value: The GoodbyeAnimation Mode is left when vehicle state "Standfunktion" or "Parken" is left.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Due to technical conditions the definition of several substa

UML:TaggedValue.value: Due to technical conditions the definition of several substates or/and additional transition conditions may necessary (definition must be agreed between supplier and BMW).

UML:ClassifierRole.name: When vehicle state Fahren or Prfen/Analyse/Diagnose is reac

UML:TaggedValue.value: When vehicle state Fahren or Prfen/Analyse/Diagnose is reached during Welcome Animation, HMI must be shown immediately (when HMI is already loaded).

UML:ClassifierRole.name: When Carsharing is coded, the PIN input mask must be shown i

UML:TaggedValue.value: When Carsharing is coded, the PIN input mask must be shown instead of the Standby Screen.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Goodbye Animation must be replayed after vehicle state h

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Goodbye Animation must be replayed after vehicle state has changed from "Wohnen" to "Standfunktion" or directly to "Parken".

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Sleep Mode
In Communication mode the following functions must be provid

UML:TaggedValue.value: In Communication mode the following functions must be provided: Mode 0 + communication readiness, Busmaster functionalities, Full Powermaster functionality - CAN must be woken up - Gateway function according to specified behaviour

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Entertainment Mode is entered when the customer uses sev

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Entertainment Mode is entered when the customer uses several hardkey buttons while Standby Screen is shown during Wohnen state. Which hardkeys cause the entering of Entertainment Mode, is specified in PWF_HU_usecaselist_vx.pdf. It is also defined which HMI screen is shown when a hardkey is pushed for user-on.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The reaction of the system on several customer interaction d

UML:TaggedValue.value: The reaction of the system on several customer interaction during several states is agreed with BMW ABK in the list PWF_HU_usecaselist_vx.pdf. This list is provided to the supplier by BMW.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Active Applications/Functions: Supply of the CAN-receiver a

UML:TaggedValue.value: Active Applications/Functions: Supply of the CAN-receiver and of the Ethernet Bus Wakeup unit and necessary elements for wakeup

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Tempshutdown Mode
The Powerdown Mode is a diagnosis mode where the Head Unit h

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Powerdown Mode is a diagnosis mode where the Head Unit has to be in Sleep Mode within five seconds.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: Events or precondition to achieve this state: Busses are no

UML:TaggedValue.value: Events or precondition to achieve this state: Busses are not active (CAN, Ethernet,...), HU is off

UML:ClassifierRole.name: For further information, refer to DOC31 LH Diagnose.

UML:TaggedValue.value: For further information, refer to DOC31 LH Diagnose.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The Head Unit must provide several user interaction details

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Head Unit must provide several user interaction details for the PWF master. This information is used for changing or not changing the vehicle state.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The RSE has to implement a low power mode.

UML:TaggedValue.value: The RSE has to implement a low power mode.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The RSE states are independent from the vehicle states. Exce

UML:TaggedValue.value: The RSE states are independent from the vehicle states. Exception: When Wohnen is switched off, RSE is also switched off. It can be switched on again by push on I/O-Button on RSE/Fond monitor. When switching on RSE, it requests the partial network "Entertainment". When RSE is switched off, it must release the request for partial network "Entertainment". Due to energy efficiency requirements in PWF concept, the RSE shall be internally shut down when it is not used during drive.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The RSE must also support user interaction detection and par

UML:TaggedValue.value: The RSE must also support user interaction detection and partial networking.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: All implemneted clients for services from the car network mu

UML:TaggedValue.value: All implemneted clients for services from the car network must be provide full information about states and events.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The communication between lifcycle module and the consumer a

UML:TaggedValue.value: The communication between lifcycle module and the consumer applications must be logged.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: All received lifecycle events by the headunit must be logged

UML:TaggedValue.value: All received lifecycle events by the headunit must be logged, even if they do not cause directly a lifecycle change in the headunit

UML:ClassifierRole.name: The available logging infrastructere must be used to log all

UML:TaggedValue.value: The available logging infrastructere must be used to log all internal states and communication of the lifecycle module, see module log and trace.

UML:ClassifierRole.name: All Lifecycle state changes must be logged with the name of

UML:TaggedValue.value: All Lifecycle state changes must be logged with the name of the old state, the new state and the reason which causes the state change.

GENIVI SW Requirements
The Lifecycle SW components defined in the GENIVI Compliance

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Lifecycle SW components defined in the GENIVI Compliance Spec Node State Manager, Node Startup Controller and Node Health Monitor shall be used.

UML:TaggedValue.value: The Lifecycle Statemachine, provided by BMW, must be integrated into the system.
